		"text"		: "1\n00:00:03,180 --> 00:00:07,340\nWelcome to Storyline Online, brought to\nyou by the SAG-AFTRA Foundation.\n\n2\n00:00:07,340 --> 00:00:11,840\nI'm Rashida Jones, and today I'm going to\nread Please Please the Bees,\n\n3\n00:00:11,960 --> 00:00:14,800\nwritten and illustrated by Gerald Kelly.\n\n4\n00:00:16,700 --> 00:00:21,340\nBenedict was a creature of habit. He liked to do the same thing every day.\n\n5\n00:00:21,340 --> 00:00:25,380\nEvery morning he woke up at the same time. Every morning he stretched.\n\n6\n00:00:25,440 --> 00:00:28,080\nHe scratched. He yawned a\ngreat yawn.\n\n7\n00:00:29,540 --> 00:00:34,640\nEvery morning the bees delivered three\njars full of honey.\n\n8\n00:00:34,640 --> 00:00:41,820\nBenedict ate the same breakfast he'd\neaten since he was just a fuzzy cub:\ntoast with honey and tea with extra\nhoney.\n\n9\n00:00:41,840 --> 00:00:53,020\nNext came his daily routine: practicing, perfecting his honey cake recipe, \nknitting, and running errands.\n\n10\n00:00:53,060 --> 00:00:59,000\nAt night he'd read then have one last\ncup of honey tea before bed. Life was sweet.\n\n11\n00:01:00,520 --> 00:01:04,900\nUntil one morning... one morning\nthings weren't the same.\n\n12\n00:01:04,920 --> 00:01:09,360\nIn fact, something terribly un-same had happened.\n\n13\n00:01:11,520 --> 00:01:16,140\nThere was no more honey. The bees had\ngone on strike!\n\n14\n00:01:17,600 --> 00:01:23,680\nBenedict's breakfast wasn't the same\nwithout honey.\nWithout his honey tea, he couldn't knit.\n\n15\n00:01:23,800 --> 00:01:28,200\nPractice was dreadful. He didn't even bother with the errands.\n\n16\n00:01:28,820 --> 00:01:36,920\nBenedict became deeply discouraged. Just then he heard someone say, \"Hey, you! In the fur coat!\"\n\n17\n00:01:36,920 --> 00:01:42,100\nIt was a very small bee with a remarkably loud voice. \"We need to talk!\" said the bee.\n\n18\n00:01:42,820 --> 00:01:50,100\n\"Talk? Hmmph!\" grumbled Benedict. \"I let you all live in my yard. All I ask is for a few jars of honey.\"\n\n19\n00:01:50,100 --> 00:01:53,060\n\"You should be grateful. Not go on strike!\"\n\n20\n00:01:53,060 --> 00:01:59,040\n\"A few jars?\" said the bee. \"Buddy, we deliver three jars of honey to you every day.\"\n\n21\n00:01:59,040 --> 00:02:02,180\n\"Every month! Every year! Do the math, Einstein!”\n\n22\n00:02:03,100 --> 00:02:08,300\n“The hive is a wreck!” the bee continued.  “It’s all we can do to keep the walls from falling in!\"\n\n23\n00:02:08,300 --> 00:02:11,240\n\"The roof leaks. Wind blows through the cracks.\"\n\n24\n00:02:11,800 --> 00:02:15,600\n\"The last three queens up and quit on us because of the lousy work conditions.\"\n\n25\n00:02:15,600 --> 00:02:20,540\nThe bee showed Benedict the garden. \"Look!\" the bee said. \"Weeds everywhere.\"\n\n26\n00:02:20,680 --> 00:02:26,920\n\"We have to fly miles away just to find enough flowers to make our honey. So we voted to strike.”\n\n27\n00:02:27,600 --> 00:02:34,600\n\"You’re taking us for granted,” the bee declared. “You want honey? Things need to change. It’s up to you, bear.”\n\n28\n00:02:34,960 --> 00:02:38,120\nAnd with that, the very small bee flew off.\n\n29\n00:02:40,440 --> 00:02:46,280\nThe thought of losing his honey sent a chill down Benedict’s spine. He had a lot to think about.\n\n30\n00:02:46,280 --> 00:02:54,320\n“Maybe I’ve been too selfish,” Benedict said to himself. “I never thought about what the bees need. \nBut how am I going to make this right?\"\n\n31\n00:02:54,400 --> 00:03:02,460\nSo he did some research. He did a little shopping.\nAnd he did a lot of work.\n\n32\n00:03:03,140 --> 00:03:06,200\nBenedict even learned how to harvest honey.\n\n33\n00:03:12,280 --> 00:03:16,520\n“I suppose it’s a bit rude to expect them to do it all themselves,” he thought.\n\n34\n00:03:17,740 --> 00:03:23,260\nFinally, he was ready to show the bees all the work he’d done. What would they think?\n\n35\n00:03:23,560 --> 00:03:29,920\nHe held his breath as he waited. Then he heard the remarkably loud voice of the very small bee…\n\n36\n00:03:31,580 --> 00:03:35,320\n“DROP THE SIGNS, GIRLS! TIME TO GET BACK TO WORK!”\n\n37\n00:03:38,280 --> 00:03:43,180\nThese days, Benedict is still a creature of habit.\nHe still has his daily routine,\n\n38\n00:03:43,520 --> 00:03:49,080\nbut he doesn’t take the honey for granted anymore.\nHe knows his life is sweet...\n\n39\n00:03:49,320 --> 00:03:53,100\nbut now it's even sweeter...\n\n40\n00:03:53,360 --> 00:03:55,000\nfor everyone.\n\n41\n00:03:56,040 --> 00:03:57,300\nThe end.\n\n42\n00:03:57,780 --> 00:04:04,880\nI really enjoyed this book because it's all about being able to live with each other, and respect each other,\n\n43\n00:04:05,080 --> 00:04:10,040\nand give and take. Because that's the best part about being in a community,\n\n44\n00:04:10,040 --> 00:04:15,300\nis being able to live together and have everybody's life be sweet at the same time.\n\n45\n00:04:17,180 --> 00:04:21,680\nThank you for watching Storyline Online. \nMake sure to watch all our other stories.\n\n46\n00:04:21,680 --> 00:04:24,180\nKeep watching and keep reading!",
