		"text"		: "1\n00:00:03,140 --> 00:00:06,340\nWelcome to Storyline Online, brought to you by the SAG-AFTRA Foundation.\n\n2\n00:00:06,540 --> 00:00:10,820\nI'm Kristen Bell, and today I will be reading \"Quackenstein Hatches a Family,\"\n\n3\n00:00:10,980 --> 00:00:15,580\nwritten by Sudipta Bardhan-Quallen and illustrated by Brian T. Jones.\n\n4\n00:00:15,820 --> 00:00:20,160\nIn the darkest corner of the zoo\nThere stood a gloomy shack.\n\n5\n00:00:20,460 --> 00:00:26,660\nA nearby scrawl read\n\"Keep out all!! Just leave me be! Signed, Quack\"\n\n6\n00:00:27,380 --> 00:00:29,920\nMost creatures lived\nIn packs and herds,\n\n7\n00:00:30,180 --> 00:00:32,140\nIn gaggles, bloats, and litters.\n\n8\n00:00:32,900 --> 00:00:34,940\nBut all alone\nThere on his own\n\n9\n00:00:35,240 --> 00:00:37,540\nPoor Quackenstein grew bitter.\n\n10\n00:00:37,920 --> 00:00:42,280\nHe was the hermit of the zoo\nAnd faced a lonely struggle.\n\n11\n00:00:42,560 --> 00:00:45,540\n\"It isn't fair!\nMy nest is bare!\"\n\n12\n00:00:45,700 --> 00:00:47,480\nHe had no one to snuggle.\n\n13\n00:00:47,880 --> 00:00:51,840\nQuack passed the nursery one day, \nWhere babies laughed and tumbled.\n\n14\n00:00:52,160 --> 00:00:57,100\n\"Everyone has some someone, \nExcept for me,\" he mumbled.\n\n15\n00:00:57,380 --> 00:01:02,480\nHe spied a small, secluded nook.\nOn impulse, he proceeded.\n\n16\n00:01:02,880 --> 00:01:05,780\nHe bumped his head.\n\"A sign!\" It read:\n\n17\n00:01:05,840 --> 00:01:09,040\nOrphaned eggs, homes needed.\n\n18\n00:01:11,140 --> 00:01:15,640\nQuack hatched a plan and crept ahead.\nThis duck would not be stopped.\n\n19\n00:01:15,840 --> 00:01:18,640\nOn shaky legs,\nHe chose an egg\n\n20\n00:01:18,760 --> 00:01:21,360\nAnd cackled: I'll adopt!\n\n21\n00:01:22,040 --> 00:01:25,960\nQuack set it on his empty nest.\nHe kept his prize protected.\n\n22\n00:01:26,320 --> 00:01:28,680\nHe'd gently coo,\n\"Dear ducky-poo,\n\n23\n00:01:28,700 --> 00:01:30,780\nYou'll never be neglected!\"\n\n24\n00:01:31,700 --> 00:01:36,180\nThen on one dark and stormy night,\nThe hour had arrived.\n\n25\n00:01:36,400 --> 00:01:39,380\nQuack heard a crack--\nHe stumbled back\n\n26\n00:01:39,600 --> 00:01:41,960\nAnd shouted: It's alive!\n\n27\n00:01:42,580 --> 00:01:47,180\nJust then a small beak broke the shell!\nQuack's heart thumped in his chest,\n\n28\n00:01:47,500 --> 00:01:50,820\nBut then two paws\nWith sharp, curved claws\n\n29\n00:01:50,880 --> 00:01:53,820\nThrust through and stabbed the nest.\n\n30\n00:01:54,580 --> 00:02:01,200\n\"I've hatched... a monster! You're no duck,\"\nQuack screeched, and went quite pale.\n\n31\n00:02:01,560 --> 00:02:04,660\nThe thing had fur\nAnd legs with spurs\n\n32\n00:02:04,760 --> 00:02:07,660\nAnd some poor beaver's tail.\n\n33\n00:02:07,900 --> 00:02:10,760\nThe creature lurched. Quack gasped,\n\"Stay back!\"\n\n34\n00:02:10,960 --> 00:02:13,000\nThe beast paid him no heed.\n\n35\n00:02:13,280 --> 00:02:16,040\nQuack tried to hide.\nHe ran outside,\n\n36\n00:02:16,360 --> 00:02:17,960\nAlarmed and rubber-kneed.\n\n37\n00:02:18,500 --> 00:02:23,460\nQuack shrieked and sprightly dove behind\nSome logs out on the water.\n\n38\n00:02:23,780 --> 00:02:26,480\nBut Quack got pushed\nAnd saw he'd smushed\n\n39\n00:02:26,680 --> 00:02:28,760\nAn angry romp of otters.\n\n40\n00:02:29,180 --> 00:02:33,540\nDrenched, the poor duck ducked behind\nA mama heron reading.\n\n41\n00:02:33,780 --> 00:02:37,680\nHer babies screamed.\nThe thing's claws gleamed.\n\n42\n00:02:38,000 --> 00:02:39,980\nIt leered and kept proceeding.\n\n43\n00:02:40,340 --> 00:02:44,500\nQuack shushed the rowdy heron hedge.\nBut birds just ran off blind.\n\n44\n00:02:44,780 --> 00:02:47,240\nThey fled in shock\nToward cuddling crocs--\n\n45\n00:02:47,580 --> 00:02:49,560\nSoon all were intertwined.\n\n46\n00:02:50,080 --> 00:02:54,600\nQuack rashly rushed and promptly crushed\nA hugging husk of hares.\n\n47\n00:02:55,060 --> 00:02:58,440\n\"My fault!\" Quack cried,\nBut then he spied\n\n48\n00:02:58,680 --> 00:03:00,540\nThe monster's chilling glare.\n\n49\n00:03:00,780 --> 00:03:04,740\nSo quickly Quack hid in a cave,\nBut there he'd made an error.\n\n50\n00:03:05,060 --> 00:03:07,560\nA furry shape\nBlocked his escape.\n\n51\n00:03:07,560 --> 00:03:10,100\n\"I'm trapped!\" he screeched in terror.\n\n52\n00:03:10,340 --> 00:03:15,740\nThe thing then snarled, \"Oh, there you are!\"\nIt stalked the trembling fowl.\n\n53\n00:03:15,880 --> 00:03:18,620\nWith sharp claws bared\nAnd shoulders squared,\n\n54\n00:03:18,800 --> 00:03:20,400\nIt leaped in with a growl!\n\n55\n00:03:20,780 --> 00:03:25,380\nIts paws soon squeezed the cringing duck,\nAnd Quack thought, \"This is BAD!\"\n\n56\n00:03:25,540 --> 00:03:28,760\nHis spirit broke\nWhen someone spoke--\n\n57\n00:03:28,980 --> 00:03:31,780\nThe thing said: Hello Dad!\n\n58\n00:03:32,100 --> 00:03:37,280\nQuack could feel his cold heart melt,\nAnd how his stomach fluttered.\n\n59\n00:03:37,900 --> 00:03:41,240\n\"You chased me through\nThe great big zoo\n\n60\n00:03:41,460 --> 00:03:43,860\nTo be with me?\" he sputtered.\n\n61\n00:03:44,120 --> 00:03:49,500\nThe creature beamed, \"Yes, Daddy, yes!\"\nQuack's heart began to sing.\n\n62\n00:03:49,800 --> 00:03:52,560\n\"Come, son,\" he squawked,\nAnd off they walked,\n\n63\n00:03:52,800 --> 00:03:55,680\nIn step, and paw in wing.\n\n64\n00:03:56,460 --> 00:04:00,300\nThen in the corner of the zoo\nThat once housed Quackenstein,\n\n65\n00:04:00,740 --> 00:04:03,480\nA space was cleared\nAnd there appeared\n\n66\n00:04:03,700 --> 00:04:05,480\nA shiny brand-new sign.\n\n67\n00:04:05,720 --> 00:04:09,980\n\"Welcome to our happy home. Come by to visit us. \nLove, Quack\" it read.\n\n68\n00:04:10,320 --> 00:04:15,160\nBelow, it said:\n\"And his son, Platypus.\"\n\n69\n00:04:15,940 --> 00:04:17,440\nThe end.\n\n70\n00:04:17,780 --> 00:04:21,600\nI chose this book because I really like the rhyming,\n\n71\n00:04:21,820 --> 00:04:24,660\nI really like the language, the big words,\n\n72\n00:04:24,860 --> 00:04:32,060\nbut more importantly, I love that Quack felt lonely and he decided to solve his problem\n\n73\n00:04:32,220 --> 00:04:35,820\nby adopting one of these eggs that didn't have a family.\n\n74\n00:04:36,080 --> 00:04:42,620\nAnd even though he was initially scared, because the platypus that came out of the egg looked different than him,\n\n75\n00:04:42,900 --> 00:04:47,640\nhe eventually realized that it was the perfect way to make a family for himself,\n\n76\n00:04:47,800 --> 00:04:53,340\nand realized that he needed that platypus just as much as the platypus needed him.\n\n77\n00:04:53,620 --> 00:04:57,160\nThank you for watching Storyline Online. Make sure to check out all of our stories.\n\n78\n00:04:57,380 --> 00:04:59,700\nKeep watching and keep reading.",
