		"title"		: "The Tooth",
		"text"		: "1\n00:00:00,719 --> 00:00:09,809\nHi everybody, welcome to Storyline Online. It's brought to you by the Screen Actors Guild Foundation.\n\n2\n00:00:09,809 --> 00:00:22,880\nI'm Annette Bening and I'm here today to read The Tooth, written by Avi Slodovnik and illustrated by Manon Gauthier.\n\n3\n00:00:22,880 --> 00:00:27,380\nMarissa's love of candy finally caught up with her.\n\n4\n00:00:27,380 --> 00:00:34,840\nThat morning she woke up with a toothache and instead of bringing her to school, her mother took her to the dentist.\n\n5\n00:00:35,300 --> 00:00:42,720\nMarissa didn't often go downtown. Columns of tall, gray buildings cast great shadows across the streets.\n\n6\n00:00:42,720 --> 00:00:50,270\nThe sky, usually bright and blue, was barely visible between the rows of endlessly tall skyscrapers.\n\n7\n00:00:50,270 --> 00:00:55,420\nMarissa and her mother walked hand-in-hand toward the dentist's office.\n\n8\n00:00:55,420 --> 00:01:04,559\nMen and women wearing long coats and long faces, their collars up and their heads down, rushed in every direction.\n\n9\n00:01:04,559 --> 00:01:07,030\nMarissa leaned closer to her mother.\n\n10\n00:01:07,030 --> 00:01:13,250\nWhen they stopped at the corner for the light to change, Marissa noticed something unusual.\n\n11\n00:01:13,250 --> 00:01:21,000\nA man with a large nose and dark eyes was sitting on a grate in the sidewalk.\n\n12\n00:01:21,000 --> 00:01:25,580\nIn front of him was an open shoebox with money inside.\n\n13\n00:01:25,580 --> 00:01:33,770\nMarissa had never seen anyone like him. She wanted to take a closer look but her mother held her hand tightly.\n\n14\n00:01:33,770 --> 00:01:39,920\nAs they crossed the street to the dentist's building, Marissa looked back and watched the man over her shoulder.\n\n15\n00:01:40,000 --> 00:01:47,000\nHe sat quietly, watching the people pass him by.\n\n16\n00:01:47,000 --> 00:01:55,000\nUp in the dentist's office they checked in with the receptionist who told them to sit in the waiting room until the dentist was ready to see them.\n\n17\n00:01:55,000 --> 00:02:00,200\nMarissa's mother sat on the couch crossing her legs and flipped through a magazine.\n\n18\n00:02:00,200 --> 00:02:08,030\nInstead of reading a book or playing with a toy, Marissa looked out the window to the busy street below.\n\n19\n00:02:08,030 --> 00:02:13,860\nThe man was still sitting on the grate. Most people walked by the man.\n\n20\n00:02:13,860 --> 00:02:18,919\nSome people, just a few, dropped coins into his shoebox.\n\n21\n00:02:18,920 --> 00:02:23,220\nOne man in a hurry actually stepped over the man.\n\n22\n00:02:25,360 --> 00:02:30,499\nFinally, after a long wait, Marissa was called into the examination room.\n\n23\n00:02:30,499 --> 00:02:34,369\nShe sat in the big chair and opened her mouth as wide as she could.\n\n24\n00:02:34,369 --> 00:02:40,989\nThe dentist saw a small, brown hole in Marissa's tooth.\n\n25\n00:02:40,989 --> 00:02:46,239\n\"That's quite a cavity,\" he said, \"the tooth will have to come out.\"\n\n26\n00:02:46,240 --> 00:02:51,960\nA few minutes later, the dentist pulled out Marissa's tooth.\n\n27\n00:02:51,960 --> 00:02:55,420\nMarissa wished she was in school.\n\n28\n00:02:55,420 --> 00:03:01,340\n\"Here's your tooth, Marissa,\" said the dentist, slipping the tiny tooth into a small, orange envelope.\n\n29\n00:03:01,340 --> 00:03:04,800\n\"Make sure to put it under your pillow,\" said her mother.\n\n30\n00:03:04,800 --> 00:03:10,619\n\"Make sure you brush your teeth twice a day, and especially after candy,\" said the dentist.\n\n31\n00:03:11,060 --> 00:03:15,899\nThey left the dentist's office and in the elevator Marissa asked her mother,\n\n32\n00:03:15,899 --> 00:03:20,409\n\"Is there really a tooth fairy?\"\n\n33\n00:03:20,409 --> 00:03:23,920\nOutside the dentist's office, the air was cool.\n\n34\n00:03:23,920 --> 00:03:31,360\nMarissa tickled the place her tooth had been with her tongue. It felt funny.\n\n35\n00:03:31,369 --> 00:03:37,059\nThey crossed the street. The man was still sitting on the sidewalk.\n\n36\n00:03:37,059 --> 00:03:42,579\nMarissa tried to get closer, but her mother held her hand tightly, like before.\n\n37\n00:03:42,580 --> 00:03:51,300\nMarissa pulled away and went up to the shoebox. There wasn't a lot of money inside.\n\n38\n00:03:51,300 --> 00:03:59,120\nMarissa held open the orange envelope and let the tooth drop into the shoebox.\n\n39\n00:03:59,120 --> 00:04:06,159\n\"Put it under your pillow tonight,\" she told the man, \"and there will be money there tomorrow.\"\n\n40\n00:04:06,160 --> 00:04:17,820\nAt first the man looked surprised. Then he smiled warmly and waved goodbye to Marissa as she and her mother walked away.\n\n41\n00:04:17,820 --> 00:04:23,240\nNow, all he needed was a pillow.\n\n42\n00:04:30,700 --> 00:04:41,240\nI used to read books to my kids all the time. They're too big now, but I hope you have a chance to talk to your teachers or maybe your mom or your dad about the book.\n\n43\n00:04:41,240 --> 00:04:51,500\nI think it's a really thoughtful book. Starts out being a trip to the dentist and it ends with a little girl meeting a homeless man.\n\n44\n00:04:51,500 --> 00:04:53,240\nAnyway, I hope you liked it, I did.",
