		"title"		: "Turkey Trouble",
		"text"		: "1\n00:00:03,540 --> 00:00:07,220\nWelcome to Storyline Online brought to\nyou by the SAG-AFTRA Foundation.\n\n2\n00:00:07,480 --> 00:00:10,980\nI'm Marc Maron and today I'm gonna read Turkey Trouble\n\n3\n00:00:10,980 --> 00:00:14,940\nwritten by Wendi Silvano and illustrated by Lee Harper.\n\n4\n00:00:15,600 --> 00:00:18,700\nTurkey was in trouble.\nBad trouble.\n\n5\n00:00:18,900 --> 00:00:23,920\nThe kind of trouble where it’s almost Thanksgiving... and you’re the main course.\n\n6\n00:00:24,400 --> 00:00:26,880\nBut Turkey had an idea...\n\n7\n00:00:27,160 --> 00:00:31,440\nWhat if he didn’t look like a turkey?\nWhat if he looked like a horse?\n\n8\n00:00:31,720 --> 00:00:35,980\nSurely Farmer Jake wouldn’t eat a horse for Thanksgiving.\n\n9\n00:00:36,180 --> 00:00:41,280\nHis costume wasn’t bad.\nIn fact, Turkey looked just like a horse...\n\n10\n00:00:42,280 --> 00:00:43,820\nalmost.\n\n11\n00:00:44,440 --> 00:00:49,800\n“Mooooo” said Cow. “Stop horsing around, Turkey.”\n\n12\n00:00:50,040 --> 00:00:53,540\n“How’d you know it was me?” moaned Turkey.\n\n13\n00:00:53,980 --> 00:01:00,660\n“Too short,” said Cow.\n“Gobble, gobble,” grumbled Turkey.\n\n14\n00:01:00,900 --> 00:01:04,480\nBut looking at Cow gave Turkey a new idea.\n\n15\n00:01:04,980 --> 00:01:09,220\nSurely Farmer Jake wouldn’t eat a cow for Thanksgiving.\n\n16\n00:01:09,800 --> 00:01:15,820\nHis costume wasn’t bad.\nIn fact, Turkey looked just like a cow...\n\n17\n00:01:16,400 --> 00:01:18,140\nalmost.\n\n18\n00:01:18,480 --> 00:01:22,880\n“Oink, oink, oink,” snorted Pig. “Holy cow! Is that you, Turkey?”\n\n19\n00:01:23,220 --> 00:01:25,360\n“How’d you know it was me?” groaned Turkey.\n\n20\n00:01:25,560 --> 00:01:31,780\n“Too skinny,” said Pig.\n“Gobble, gobble,” grumbled Turkey.\n\n21\n00:01:32,020 --> 00:01:35,240\nBut looking at Pig gave Turkey a new idea.\n\n22\n00:01:35,440 --> 00:01:39,380\nSurely Farmer Jake wouldn’t eat a pig for Thanksgiving.\n\n23\n00:01:39,560 --> 00:01:45,060\nHis costume wasn’t bad.\nIn fact, Turkey looked just like a pig...\n\n24\n00:01:46,600 --> 00:01:48,180\nalmost.\n\n25\n00:01:48,460 --> 00:01:50,640\n“Baaaa, baaaa,” bleated Sheep.\n\n26\n00:01:50,900 --> 00:01:52,900\n“Quit being a ham, Turkey.”\n\n27\n00:01:53,060 --> 00:01:56,220\n“How’d you know it was me?” wailed Turkey.\n\n28\n00:01:56,560 --> 00:02:02,540\n“Too clean,” said Sheep.\n“Gobble, gobble,” grumbled Turkey.\n\n29\n00:02:02,820 --> 00:02:06,160\nBut looking at Sheep gave Turkey a new idea.\n\n30\n00:02:06,700 --> 00:02:11,160\nSurely Farmer Jake wouldn’t eat a sheep for Thanksgiving.\n\n31\n00:02:11,360 --> 00:02:16,400\nHis costume wasn’t bad.\nIn fact, Turkey looked just like a sheep...\n\n32\n00:02:17,100 --> 00:02:19,100\nalmost.\n\n33\n00:02:21,940 --> 00:02:27,440\n“Cock-a-doodle-doo!” crowed Rooster. “Baaa-d idea, Turkey.”\n\n34\n00:02:27,680 --> 00:02:30,900\n“How’d you know it was me?” howled Turkey.\n\n35\n00:02:30,900 --> 00:02:38,180\n“Too brown,” squawked Rooster.\n“Gobble, gobble,” grumbled Turkey.\n\n36\n00:02:38,940 --> 00:02:42,560\nBut looking at Rooster gave Turkey a new idea.\n\n37\n00:02:42,740 --> 00:02:45,980\nIn fact, it was his best idea yet.\n\n38\n00:02:46,460 --> 00:02:51,300\nHe already looked a lot like Rooster. This costume would be easy!\n\n39\n00:02:51,700 --> 00:02:56,540\nSurely Farmer Jake wouldn’t eat a rooster for Thanksgiving...\n\n40\n00:02:56,540 --> 00:02:58,540\n...or would he?\n\n41\n00:02:58,860 --> 00:03:06,680\nRooster might be his next choice, Turkey worried, since roosters and turkeys look so much alike.\n\n42\n00:03:07,620 --> 00:03:10,240\nOh, gobble, gobble!\n\n43\n00:03:10,600 --> 00:03:13,480\nFarmer Jake came into the barn.\n\n44\n00:03:13,480 --> 00:03:18,020\n“Turkey, turkey, turkey?\n\n45\n00:03:18,500 --> 00:03:21,160\nCome out, come out, wherever you are.”\n\n46\n00:03:21,200 --> 00:03:24,040\n“Where’s the turkey?” asked Farmer Jake’s wife.\n\n47\n00:03:24,040 --> 00:03:27,000\n“I don’t know,” he said. “I looked everywhere!”\n\n48\n00:03:27,200 --> 00:03:31,240\n“Oh, dear. What will we do without a turkey for Thanksgiving?”\n\n49\n00:03:31,480 --> 00:03:34,920\n“Well... we could always eat the rooster, I guess.”\n\n50\n00:03:35,100 --> 00:03:37,820\nOh, no, not Rooster! thought Turkey.\n\n51\n00:03:38,100 --> 00:03:41,120\nHe looked around desperately for one more idea.\n\n52\n00:03:41,300 --> 00:03:43,760\nThen, he found it...\n\n53\n00:03:43,980 --> 00:03:48,780\nHis costume wasn’t bad...\nIn fact, it was Turkey’s best yet!\n\n54\n00:03:49,660 --> 00:03:51,340\nDing-dong...\n\n55\n00:03:51,560 --> 00:03:53,560\n“Happy Thanksgiving!”\n\n56\n00:03:53,700 --> 00:03:56,600\n“Did you order a pizza?”\nasked Farmer Jake’s wife.\n\n57\n00:03:56,600 --> 00:04:00,360\n“Nope,” he said. “But it’s a good idea.”\n\n58\n00:04:00,900 --> 00:04:06,400\nSo they all sat down and gobbled up the pizza.\n\n59\n00:04:06,820 --> 00:04:11,480\nAnd it was Turkey’s best Thanksgiving ever!\n\n60\n00:04:12,020 --> 00:04:13,560\nThe end.\n\n61\n00:04:14,480 --> 00:04:17,360\nSo you know I chose this book\nbecause it's pretty funny.\n\n62\n00:04:18,040 --> 00:04:22,080\nI thought the turkey was was clever\nwith the costumes\n\n63\n00:04:22,440 --> 00:04:26,840\nand you know I think when when you're in a bit of fear and a bit of panic\n\n64\n00:04:27,200 --> 00:04:33,320\nand you have to figure out something to do to avoid something bad happening.\n\n65\n00:04:33,700 --> 00:04:37,220\nSometimes you got to think on your feet and I thought he did a pretty good job at that\n\n66\n00:04:37,220 --> 00:04:41,260\nand he saved his buddy the rooster too so he's helping everybody out\n\n67\n00:04:41,500 --> 00:04:45,020\nand everybody lives another year and just eats pizza.\n\n68\n00:04:45,020 --> 00:04:47,500\nThank you for watching Storyline Online\n\n69\n00:04:47,500 --> 00:04:49,820\nMake sure to check out all of our stories.\n\n70\n00:04:50,000 --> 00:04:52,020\nKeep watching and keep reading.",
		"avatarURL"	: "https://www.storylineonline.net/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/TurkeyTrouble.jpg",
		"mediaURL"	: "https://youtu.be/TzUS7UHXsd8",
		"isYouTube"	: true
